* Thu Jun 04 2026 Shenglong Zhu <shenglongzhu@linux.alibaba.com> - 0.1.0-1
- Init package: ship the `anolisa` CLI binary, capabilities/osbase/runtime
  manifests, OSS-targeted distribution index (built with default mirror/channel
  overridable via `--define '_anolisa_mirror ...'` / `'_anolisa_channel ...'`),
  and the execution-policy template.
- CLI commands include `env`, `list`, `status`, `logs`, `enable`, `disable`, `uninstall`, `restart`, `update`, `info`, and `doctor`.
- Environment detection covers OS, arch, kernel, distro, container runtime, and user identity.
- Component lifecycle includes preview-then-execute, integrity checks, and audit logging.
- Component manifests are declarative TOML files with multi-architecture support.
- `install-anolisa.sh` supports local, checkout, and URL modes with checksum verification and `--dry-run`.
